Palestinians to engage in ``honest discussion,'' not violence, as
they seek to resolve their differences over the Wye River
land-for-peace deal. As the president sought to get the peace
process back on track, there were indications that the Israelis
will continue to insist on delaying scheduled troop withdrawals
from Palestinian territories. (Deans, Cox News Service)
