<P>
   MIDEAST-CLINTON (Jerusalem) _ Combative and stone-faced,
President Clinton flatly denied on Sunday that he had committed
perjury, as he reluctantly interrupted his efforts to rescue the
Middle East peace plan to address an impeachment vote he said he
cannot control. By James Bennet.
</P>
<P>
   MIDEAST-CLINTON-SCENE (Jerusalem) _ President Clinton may have
left the United States on the heels of what one Israeli daily
termed a Congressional intifada, using the Arab term for uprising.
But there is no question that Clinton is engaged in a critical
salvage mission for the faltering peace effort. By Deborah Sontag.
</P>
<P>
   NAZI-SLAVELABOR (Frankfurt, Germany) _ Spurred on by Germany's
new Social Democratic government and a huge trans-Atlantic merger,
Germany's banks and industrial conglomerates are urgently trying to
devise a broad new plan to compensate Holocaust survivors and
millions of Poles, Russians, and other Europeans enslaved by the
Nazis. The corporations, from Deutsche Bank AG to Siemens and
DaimlerChrysler AG, want to free themselves from a slew of new
American class-action lawsuits alleging that they profited by
collaborating with the Nazis during World War II. The controversy
also threatens to pull in U.S. government officials who, for now,
are taking a cautious approach to direct involvement. By Barry
Meier and Edmund L. Andrews.
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-COPING (Mozhaivsk) _ How wards of the Russian state
manage to survive in a calamity-prone economy. The answer is, as
usual, a mish-mash involving the kindness of strangers and a dash
of native ingenuity. By Celestine Bohlen. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   IRELAND-NEUTRALITY (Dublin) _ The Irish government is moving
cautiously, but unmistakably, toward a relaxation of Ireland's
bedrock national policy: the military neutrality it has proudly
maintained since gaining independence from Britain 76 years ago. By
James F. Clarity. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   AFRICA-CHRISTIANS (Harare, Zimbabwe) _ The Church in Africa
refuses to accept an African denomination that allows polygamy
among its clergy. By Gustav Niebuhr. 700 words.
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   (Coded a)
</P>
