<P>
   Add N.Y. Times News Service budget for papers of Monday, Dec.
14:
</P>
<P>
   CULTURE
</P>
<P>
   (Coded e)
</P>
<P>
   PRINCE-EGYPT-CREATOR (Hollywood) _ What makes executives
responsible for ``The Prince of Egypt'' nervous is that this
animated film is a somber musical saga designed for adults and
children who are not toddlers. One of its creators says he he has
sought to make a film that borrows far less from the cartoon
tradition and far more from David Lean's ``Lawrence of Arabia,''
and even from the French impressionist Claude Monet and from the
biblical etchings of the 19th-century illustrator Gustave Dore. By
Bernard Weinraub.
</P>
<P>
   CRITICS-FILM-AWARDS (Hollywood) _ In a vote that could
foreshadow next year's Academy Awards, on Saturday night the Los
Angeles Film Critics Association named ``Saving Private Ryan'' best
picture of the year, and it voted Steven Spielberg best director.
By Bernard Weinraub.
</P>
<P>
   GENERATION-BOOK-REVIEW (Undated) _ ``The Greatest Generation.''
Tom Brokaw on the lives of men and women who came of age during the
Depression and World War II. Christopher Lehmann-Haupt reviews .
