<P>
   MIDEAST-IMPEACH _ JERUSALEM _ Facing Republican demands that he
admit lying before a grand jury, President Clinton insisted Sunday
that he did not perjure himself and said he will not resign. ``I
cannot admit to doing something that I am quite sure I did not
do,'' he said at a press conference with Israeli Prime Minister
Benjamin Netanyahu. Clinton urged the House to listen to ``75
percent of the American people'' and censure him instead of voting
for impeachment. Story will wrap in the day's other impeachment
developments. (Deans, Cox News Service)
</P>
