   MIDEAST-PEACE _ JERUSALEM _ President Clinton urged Israelis and
Palestinians to engage in ``honest discussion,'' not violence, as
they seek to resolve their differences over the Wye River
land-for-peace deal. As the president sought to get the peace
process back on track, there were indications that the Israelis
will continue to insist on delaying scheduled troop withdrawals
from Palestinian territories. (Deans, Cox News Service)
</P>
<P>
   MIDEAST-BILLFANS _ JERUSALEM Clinton may be in trouble on
Capitol Hill, but he is overwhelmingly popular with most Israelis.
A few months ago, a Gallup poll indicated that, if they could, more
Israelis would vote for him to be their Prime Minister than either
the man they have, Benjamin Netanyahu, or his opposition, Ehud
Barak. (Kaplow, Cox News Service) MOVED
</P>
