past 21 months, Fidelity Federal's Anita Mixon and 13 others have
been testing the thrift's computers to make sure time doesn't leave
them behind on Jan. 1, 2000. If all goes well at Fidelity Federal
and other institutions, computers will move smoothly into the 21st
century; ATMs will continue to dispense cash, your checks and
payments will clear, and bank and thrift computers will remember
who you are, how much is in your account and, of course, how much
you owe. If not, hang on to your statements and receipts. (Herubin,
Palm Beach Post) MOVED
