<HEADLINE>
TEXTBOOK EXAMPLE FOR HIGH SCHOOL ATHLETES
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   In time for high school recruiting season, Marc Isenberg and
Rich Rhoads have produced a companion survival guide to their
Athlete Network Web site that should assist not only the recruitee
but his or her parents, coaches and administrators as well.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Real Athletes Guide: How to Succeed in Sports, School &AMP;
Life'' is a 208-page book available on their site
(http://athletenetwork.com) for $19.98. It can also be ordered on
Amazon's online bookstore (http://www.amazon.com) by a toll-free
number (1-800-356-9315).
</P>
<P>
   It answers questions about eligibility for NCAA, NAIA and junior
college athletes, the availability of scholarships and what to
watch out for during recruiting periods.
</P>
<P>
   Other new features on The Athlete Network site are diaries from
several athletes on different levels of competition, including one
by College of the Canyons women's basketball player Stephanie
Wasserman.
</P>
<P>
   __ Dirty trick: Get on the Falcons' bandwagon, and Atlanta
players Gene Williams and Adam Schreiber have ready ``Dirty Birds''
T-shirts (modeled by Jamal Anderson) on their new Web site
(http://www.dirtybirdsinc.com). Order three or more and get an
autographed photo of Williams.
</P>
<P>
   All of which is pretty cool if you're a Falcons fan _ except
!ital!nowhere on the site does it list the price of these
soon-to-be collectors' items.
</P>
</TEXT>
